				<p>When I moved to Utah to pursue an education I discovered these amazing things. These things called “Coding Bootcamps”. And with an elightening change in perspective I became enthrawled with the idea. For 3 months.</p>

				   <p>
			          <button
			            class="btn btn-warning btn-block"
			            type="button"
			            data-toggle="collapse"
			            data-target="#jobHistory"
			            aria-expanded="false"
			            aria-controler="jobHistory"
			          >
			            Job History
			          </button>

			          <button
			            class="btn btn-warning btn-block"
			            type="button"
			            data-toggle="collapse"
			            data-target="#education"
			            aria-expanded="false"
			            aria-controler="education"
			          >
			            Education
			          </button>
			        </p>

			        <p>
			          <div class="collapse" id="jobHistory">
			            <div class="card card-block">
			              Product Development <a  href="https://www.premier.ag/home" target= "#">Premier Ag.</a>
			            </div>
			            <div class="card card-block">
			              Social Media Analyst<a  href="https://www.nuvi.com/" target= "#">Nuvi Inc.</a>
			            </div>
			          </div>

			          <div class="collapse" id="education">
			            <div class="card card-block">
			              Big Bend Community College
			            </div>
			            <div class="card card-block">
			              Utah Valley University
			            </div>
			            <div class="card card-block">
			              Bottega Tech
			            </div>
